class ivy.container.container.Container(dict_in=None, queues=None, queue_load_sizes=None, container_combine_method='list_join', queue_timeout=None, print_limit=10, key_length_limit=None, print_indent=4, print_line_spacing=0, ivyh=None, default_key_color='green', keyword_color_dict=None, rebuild_child_containers=False, types_to_iteratively_nest=None, alphabetical_keys=True, **kwargs)[source]ÔÉÅ

Bases: ContainerWithActivations, ContainerWithCreation, ContainerWithDataTypes, ContainerWithDevice, ContainerWithElementwise, ContainerWithGeneral, ContainerWithGradients, ContainerWithImage, ContainerWithLayers, ContainerWithLinearAlgebra, ContainerWithLosses, ContainerWithManipulation, ContainerWithNorms, ContainerWithRandom, ContainerWithSearching, ContainerWithSet, ContainerWithSorting, ContainerWithStatistical, ContainerWithUtility

__add__(other)[source]ÔÉÅ

ivy.Container special method for the add operator, calling operator.add for each of the corresponding leaves of the two containers.

Examples

With Number instances at the leaves:

>>> x = ivy.Container(a=1, b=2)
>>> y = ivy.Container(a=3, b=4)
>>> z = x + y
>>> print(z)
{
    a: 4,
    b: 6
}

With ivy.Array instances at the leaves:

>>> x = ivy.Container(a=ivy.array([1, 2, 3]),                              b=ivy.array([2, 3, 4]))
>>> y = ivy.Container(a=ivy.array([4, 5, 6]),                               b=ivy.array([5, 6, 7]))
>>> z = x + y
>>> print(z)
{
    a: ivy.array([5, 7, 9]),
    b: ivy.array([7, 9, 11])
}

With a mix of ivy.Container and ivy.Array instances:

>>> x = ivy.Container(a=ivy.array([[4.], [5.], [6.]]),                              b=ivy.array([[5.], [6.], [7.]]))
>>> y = ivy.array([[1.1, 2.3, -3.6]])
>>> z = x + y
>>> print(z)
{
    a: ivy.array([[5.1, 6.3, 0.4],
                  [6.1, 7.3, 1.4],
                  [7.1, 8.3, 2.4]]),
    b: ivy.array([[6.1, 7.3, 1.4],
                  [7.1, 8.3, 2.4],
                  [8.1, 9.3, 3.4]])
}
__init__(dict_in=None, queues=None, queue_load_sizes=None, container_combine_method='list_join', queue_timeout=None, print_limit=10, key_length_limit=None, print_indent=4, print_line_spacing=0, ivyh=None, default_key_color='green', keyword_color_dict=None, rebuild_child_containers=False, types_to_iteratively_nest=None, alphabetical_keys=True, **kwargs)[source]ÔÉÅ

Initialize container object from input dict representation.

Parameters

  • dict_in ‚Äì the dictionary the container should wrap around. Default is None.

  • queues ‚Äì Sequence of multiprocessing queues, each of which returns containers. This enables the current container to be passed around asynchronously while waiting for data. Default is None.

  • queue_load_sizes ‚Äì Size of leading dimension of the containers returned by each queue. Default is None.

  • container_combine_method ‚Äì The method to use for combining containers arriving from different queues. Default is ivy.Container.list_join

  • queue_timeout ‚Äì The timeout when waiting for containers to arrive from the queues. Default is global.

  • print_limit ‚Äì The total array size limit when printing the container. Default is 10.

  • key_length_limit ‚Äì The maximum key length when printing the container. Default is None.

  • print_indent ‚Äì The number of whitespaces to use for indenting when printing the container. Default is 4.

  • print_line_spacing ‚Äì The number of extra newlines to use between keys when printing the container. Default is 0.

  • ivyh ‚Äì Handle to ivy module to use for the calculations. Default is None, which results in the global ivy.

  • default_key_color ‚Äì The default key color for printing the container to the terminal. Default is ‚Äògreen‚Äô.

  • keyword_color_dict ‚Äì A dict mapping keywords to their termcolor color codes for printing the container. (Default value = None)

  • rebuild_child_containers ‚Äì Whether to rebuild container found in dict_in with these constructor params. Default is False, in which case the original container are kept as are.

  • types_to_iteratively_nest ‚Äì The data types to nest iteratively in the dict structure, each type must be iterable. Default is None.

  • alphabetical_keys ‚Äì Whether to sort the container keys alphabetically, or preserve the dict order. Default is True.

  • kwargs ‚Äì keyword arguments for dict creation. Default is None.
